# D22_DEPMAP_CRISPR_SOS1_KRAS_v1
# Pre-registration: DepMap CRISPR essentiality — SOS1/RAF1/SHP2 in KRAS-stratified LUAD + BRAF-V600E SKCM
# Date: 2026-06-08
# Status: PRE-REGISTERED — do not load CRISPRGeneEffect.csv by KRAS status before this commit

## Scientific background

D21 revealed that SOS1 is the top structural DAMPER in KRAS-MT LUAD (z_dr=+4.184 vs
z_dr=−0.193 in KRAS-WT LUAD). SOS1 (Son of Sevenless 1) is a guanine nucleotide
exchange factor (GEF) that catalyzes GDP→GTP exchange on RAS proteins. In KRAS-MT
tumors, constitutive KRAS-GTP abolishes the need for SOS1 in steady-state signaling,
but SOS1 remains required for:
  (1) Amplitude amplification — SOS1 creates positive feedback through the
      RAS/SOS1/GRB2 scaffold that sustains KRAS-GTP levels above the threshold
      for ERK/PI3K activation at the magnitude required for tumor maintenance.
  (2) Allosteric positive cooperativity — the second (allosteric) site on SOS1
      is specifically activated by KRAS-GTP (not HRAS/NRAS), creating a
      KRAS-specific feedforward loop absent in KRAS-WT cells.
  (3) BI-3406 validation — clinical-stage SOS1-KRAS inhibitor selectively
      active in KRAS-MT cancers (Phase 1, Boehringer Ingelheim 2022).

The structural DAMPER prediction (SOS1 becomes MORE coexpression-central in KRAS-MT)
is paradoxical by classic network logic: if KRAS is constitutively active, why does
its GEF become more structurally central? The IRDME framework predicts that SOS1's
structural elevation reflects its role in the positive feedback amplitude circuit,
not simple upstream activation.

D22 tests whether the structural prediction (SOS1 elevated DAMPER in KRAS-MT) is
validated by functional genetic evidence (SOS1 CRISPR essentiality in KRAS-MT cells).

CRITICAL CONTROL — pathway-load confound:
If KRAS-MT tumors simply require MORE of ALL RAS-pathway components (RAF1, MEK1, etc.),
then SOS1 essentiality would increase in KRAS-MT as a non-specific pathway load effect.
D22 pre-registers simultaneous comparison of SOS1 vs RAF1 (direct KRAS effector) and
SHP2/PTPN11 (upstream RAS activator, different mechanism). If SOS1 differential is
larger than RAF1 differential AND larger than SHP2 differential, the SOS1 finding is
specific to GEF function, not generic pathway load.

BRAF-V600E SKCM cross-cancer control (H3):
BRAF-V600E bypasses RAS entirely (directly activates MEK). In BRAF-V600E SKCM,
SOS1 should NOT become more essential because KRAS is not the activated driver.
This tests whether the SOS1 signal is specific to KRAS activation or generalizes
to any hyperactivated MAPK pathway.

## Data

CRISPRGeneEffect.csv (DepMap 23Q4 or latest available)
  -- Index: ACH-XXXXXX cell line IDs
  -- Columns: "GENE (EntrezID)" format
  -- Genes of interest: SOS1 (6654), RAF1 (5894), PTPN11 (5781), KRAS (3845), BRAF (673)
  -- CERES score convention: more negative = more essential

Cell line annotation:
  Lineage: PRISM meta file (prism-repurposing-20q2-secondary-screen-cell-line-info.csv)
    LUAD: primary_tissue == "lung", secondary_tissue == "lung_NSC" (non-small cell)
    SKCM: primary_tissue == "skin", secondary_tissue == "melanoma"
  Mutation status: curated from CCLE/DepMap literature annotations
    KRAS-MT LUAD: cell lines with documented KRAS G12X/G13D/Q61X mutations
    KRAS-WT LUAD: cell lines documented as KRAS wild-type (may have other drivers)
    BRAF-V600E SKCM: cell lines with documented BRAF V600E mutation
    BRAF-WT SKCM: cell lines documented as BRAF wild-type (may have NRAS mutations)

Pre-registered curated mutation annotation (from CCLE literature, COSMIC, published reports):

KRAS-MT LUAD cell lines:
  A549 (KRAS G12S), NCI-H358 (KRAS G12C), NCI-H441 (KRAS G12V),
  NCI-H2009 (KRAS G12A), NCI-H1792 (KRAS G12C), NCI-H23 (KRAS G12C),
  NCI-H1373 (KRAS G12C), HCC44 (KRAS G12C), NCI-H2122 (KRAS G12C),
  NCI-H1734 (KRAS G12D), NCI-H2087 (KRAS G12V), NCI-H460 (KRAS Q61H),
  NCI-H2291 (KRAS G12D), SW1573 (KRAS G12C), NCI-H1395 (KRAS G12C),
  LU65 (KRAS G12C), NCI-H2030 (KRAS G12C), CALU1 (KRAS G12C),
  NCI-H2347 (KRAS G12D), HCC2814 (KRAS G12V)

KRAS-WT LUAD cell lines (excluding EGFR-MT to match D21 design):
  NCI-H1299 (KRAS-WT, NRAS Q61K), NCI-H1437 (KRAS-WT), NCI-H322 (KRAS-WT),
